  title: 'Indian SME Exporters: How AI Business Intelligence Is Changing the Margin Game',
  metaDescription: 'Indian SME exporters face rising freight costs, rupee volatility, and margin pressure from Western buyers. AskBiz gives you hands-on AI that tells you exactly where your margins stand.',
  cluster: 'Emerging Markets',
  pillar: 'Market Intelligence',
  publishDate: '2026-04-07',
  readTime: 7,
  tldr: 'Indian exporters — textiles, pharmaceuticals, jewellery, IT services — face a unique margin squeeze from currency exposure, long payment terms, and rising logistics costs. AskBiz gives you specific, actionable intelligence on where your margins stand and what to do about them.',
  sections: [
    { heading: 'The Indian exporter\'s margin problem in 2026', level: 2, body: 'India is one of the world\'s great export economies. But for the SME exporter — the textile manufacturer in Surat, the pharma packager in Hyderabad, the jewellery house in Jaipur — the margin environment in 2026 is under pressure. Freight costs remain elevated. Western buyers are squeezing prices. The rupee has been volatile. And the cost of credit for working capital has risen. If you are not tracking your margin at SKU level in real time, you are likely losing money on some orders and not knowing it.' },
    { heading: 'SKU-level margin analysis with AskBiz', level: 2, body: 'AskBiz lets you upload your order data, cost sheets, and freight invoices, then ask: What is my actual net margin per product after freight and currency conversion? Which buyer relationship is most profitable after payment terms are factored in? Which export market gives me the best return per unit? These are the questions that determine whether your business grows or contracts. AskBiz answers them in seconds, with your actual numbers, in INR.' },
    { heading: 'Payment term modelling for Indian exporters', level: 3, body: 'A 90-day payment term is common in export markets. But 90 days of working capital at 12% annual interest costs money — and that cost needs to come out of your margin. AskBiz can model the true cost of your payment terms by buyer and tell you which accounts are costing you more in financing than they are contributing in gross margin. This analysis used to require a CA and a spreadsheet. Now it takes 30 seconds.' },
    { heading: 'How AskBiz handles rupee volatility', level: 2, body: 'If you price in USD and your costs are in INR, every 1% move in the USD/INR rate affects your margin. AskBiz lets you ask: At the current exchange rate, what is my margin on each order? If the rupee weakens by 5%, what happens to my profitability? If it strengthens by 3%, which orders go into loss? You can run these scenarios in seconds and use the output to make faster decisions on pricing and hedging.' },
    { heading: 'The textile exporter who found 8% margin leakage with AskBiz', level: 2, body: 'A Surat-based textile exporter uploaded six months of order data to AskBiz. They asked which customer was most profitable. AskBiz identified that their second-largest buyer was actually costing them money after freight surcharges, late payment financing, and the cost of handling returns. The buyer placed large orders but the net margin was negative 2%. AskBiz found this in under a minute. Acting on it added 8% to overall business margin within a quarter.' },
  ],
  paa: [
    { q: 'Can AskBiz handle INR pricing?', a: 'Yes. AskBiz automatically detects Indian users and displays all analysis in INR.' },
    { q: 'Can AskBiz model export margins with currency exposure?', a: 'Yes. Upload your cost data in INR and revenue data in USD or GBP, and AskBiz will calculate your actual net margin accounting for currency conversion.' },
    { q: 'Is AskBiz useful for textile or pharma exporters?', a: 'Yes. AskBiz works for any business with SKU-level data. Upload your order data and cost sheets and start asking margin questions.' },
  ],
  cta: { heading: 'Know your exact margin on every order', body: 'Upload your export data and ask AskBiz where your margin is really going. In INR, with your actual costs, right now. Start free.' },
