      { heading: "Practical entry approach for UK brands", level: 2 as const, body: "Rwanda's small market size means it is best approached as part of an East Africa regional strategy — using Rwanda as a hub or test market alongside Kenya and Tanzania rather than as a standalone primary market. Options: Rwanda-based regional distributor (several well-established Rwandan trading companies have regional distribution networks covering DRC, Uganda, Burundi, and Tanzania), Special Economic Zone presence (for brands considering a regional logistics or light processing operation, Rwanda's SEZs offer attractive incentives), or DTC eCommerce (Rwanda has relatively high smartphone penetration and growing card payment adoption — direct Shopify or marketplace selling is more viable here than in some larger but less digital-ready markets)." }
