      { heading: "Strategic value as a regional transit point", level: 2 as const, body: "Beyond Zambia as an end market, its strategic position as a transit country creates logistics and warehousing opportunities. The Lusaka Freight Station and several private bonded warehouses handle transit goods destined for the DRC, Zimbabwe, Malawi, and Mozambique. UK brands establishing East/Southern Africa distribution often use Lusaka as a secondary hub alongside Nairobi — with goods arriving via Tanzania and being distributed onward through Zambia's road connections to neighbouring markets. The Zambia-DRC border crossing at Kasumbalesa is one of Africa's busiest cross-border trade points, handling billions of dollars of goods annually including significant copper and mining equipment flows." }
